The gelatinous abominations are a species of monster introduced with the Troll Warzone, said to be created by the troll, Magic Stick. They are given as a low level Slayer assignment and can be found in the Burthorpe Slayer Cave in Ewean's Grove, just south-west of the stone circle in Taverley. Spiked gauntlets, available to buy for 6 coins from any Slayer Master, are required in order to kill them. Turael offers spiked gauntlets free of charge. The gauntlets must be worn, not just be in the backpack.

Gelatinous abominations are one of the few monsters to drop gold charms for free-to-play players.

The player will automatically rip out the heart of the abomination at one life point and will only auto-rip one abomination–even if several are at one life point at the same time. You can attack another abomination during the ripping animation.

A slain gelatinous abomination does not drop its loot until about five seconds after the player receives experience from the kill. This loot despawns 30 seconds after it appears.

Update history[edit | edit source]

This information has been compiled as part of the update history project. Some updates may not be included – see here for how to help out!
  • patch 12 February 2024 (Update):
    • Rebalanced several low level monsters that were harder to kill than intended
  • patch 17 May 2021 (Update):
    • Corrected a situation which could lead to players becoming stuck in the Gelatinous Abomination Cave in the Burthorpe tutorial.
  • update 2 September 2019 (Update):
    • Burthorpe and Taverley Decluttering
  • patch 18 June 2018 (Update):
    • Made some improvements to gelatinous abominations:
      • Crush op has been removed.
      • On getting the NPC down to 1 health, the player will automatically run in to finish them.
      • Ensured attack is always the leftclick option.
      • Improved messaging about spiked gauntlets.
  • patch 12 December 2016 (Update):
    • An issue where the warning message was blocked by target information when fighting gelatinous abomination without spiked gauntlets.
  • patch 5 February 2013 (Update):
    • Players will now automatically crush abominations when they have low health as long as they have the spiked gauntlets equipped
  • update 31 January 2012 (Update):
    • Added to game.
